President Biden delivered a speech at the Portland Yacht Club in Portland, Oregon, expressing his gratitude to supporters and discussing various topics such as his decision to run for president, the importance of investing in America's infrastructure and people, the need to unite the country, and his efforts in foreign policy. He also highlighted the accomplishments of his administration, including job creation, reduction of the federal deficit, and appointments that reflect the diversity of America. President Biden emphasized the importance of addressing climate change, supporting NATO, and navigating challenges such as inflation and supply chain issues. He called for continued support in the upcoming elections to maintain Democratic control of Congress.